---
description: "Python imports, packaging, and dependency management"
type: agent-select
globs:
    - "**/*.py"
alwaysApply: false
---
- If a `ModuleNotFoundError` is encountered, first re-run the editable install (`uv sync` or `uv pip install -e .`) — a stale install is the dominant cause. The `backend` package and other local packages resolve through this install. Never set `PYTHONPATH`. For the import strategy, see `docs/dev_test_CI/DEVELOPMENT.md`.
- `uv` is the source of truth: declare runtime deps in `pyproject.toml` `[project.dependencies]` and dev/test deps under `[dependency-groups]` (`dev`, `test`). Bounds are major-capped (`>=X,<X+1`).
- `requirements.txt` is autogenerated from `uv.lock` — regenerate via `make export-reqs` after changing deps; never hand-edit. `torch` is pinned to the CPU index and excluded from the export.
